The paper proposes a novel meta-learning framework for few-shot learning that involves learning to propagate labels from labeled instances to unlabeled test instances. This involves learning a graph construction module that exploits the manifold structure in the data. The paper validates the proposed approach on multiple benchmark datasets, which suggests that it could be relevant to several sub-categories of computer science. However, given the focus on learning a generic classifier and exploiting the structure in the data, it is most likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computational linguistics (cs.CL), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
